Excuse me if I have missed something simple. 

When loading a texture from a texture atlas that has a frameX or frameY other than 0 then one must manually set the pivotX and Y when assigning that texture to an Image:

var img : Image = new Image(assets.getTexture("Dirt Block"))
img.pivotX = -img.texture.frame.x;
img.pivotY = -img.texture.frame.y;

Is there a reason why Image shouldn't take care of this for you?

Proposed change on line 195 of Textfield.:
bitmapData.draw(sNativeTextField, new Matrix(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, int(yOffset)-2),null,null,null,false);

To:
bitmapData.drawWithQuality(sNativeTextField, new Matrix(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, int(yOffset)-2),null,null,null,false,StageQuality.HIGH);

That would avoid very annoying problems when rendering .ttf embeded fonts when the stage quality is set on StageQuality.LOW (almost always on mobile).

Ask me if you need more info to reproduce :).

