In the latest version which is on the master in SVN (commit 299926ca5ab9dcdac532f314c2360f948ab84e7e), there still seems to be an issue, which has to do with issues mentioned above.

I've set up a defaultTextEditorFactory.

``` actionscript
FeathersControl.defaultTextEditorFactory = TextStyles.globalTextEditorFactory;
```

``` actionscript

public static function globalTextEditorFactory(color : uint = 0xFFFFFF, size : int = 16, fontFamily : String = "Helvetica") : ITextEditor
{
    var textEditor : StageTextTextEditor = new StageTextTextEditor();
    textEditor.autoCapitalize = AutoCapitalize.NONE;
    textEditor.autoCorrect = false;
    textEditor.color = color;
    textEditor.fontFamily = fontFamily;
    textEditor.fontSize = size;
    return textEditor;
}
```

But it seems that this fontSize doesn't compensate for Starling.contentScaleFactor.
When I tell it again explicitly what the fontSize is via the textEditorProperties, it picks it up:

``` actionscript
myTextInput.textEditorProperties.fontSize = 16;
```

I think this is a bug in the TextInput component, because it corrects for Starling's contentScaleFactor only when the font size is set via the textEditorProperties proxy (see TextInput.refreshTextEditorProperties() at line 700). But I guess it should do the same for instances of ITextEditor, but it seems it doesn't.

``` actionscript
if(propertyName == FONT_SIZE)
{
    propertyValue = (propertyValue as Number) * Starling.contentScaleFactor;
}
```

Don't shoot me if I'm wrong ;-)

I am using the AssetManager to load and remove assets on demand in my game and have loading screens that show the progress of these assets being loaded. The problem I am having is that when I am running my game on a device sometimes the onComplete event doesn't fire and the loading screen stops animation but never updates. There isn't any error that happens and if I add some kind of button that goes back resets the screen and removes the assets and  reloads them sometimes it works and sometimes it hangs.

It happens with both PNG and ATF textures and I am using nearly the same loading code that is used in the Starling scaffold demo.

``` actionscript
assetManager.loadQueue(function(ratio:Number):void
{
    if(updateCallBack){
        updateCallBack(ratio);
    }

    if (ratio == 1)
        Starling.juggler.delayCall(function():void
        {
            if(completeCallBack)
            {
                completeCallBack();
            }
        }, 0.15);
});
```

The problem seems to be that sometimes the last ratio returned is not = to 1 in all cases. I need to debug a few things to make sure that is 100% the case but I am not getting any errors so that is only suspect I have at the moment.

I was looking at the code that calculates the ratio which is using Math.min() and it seems at least plausible that the last value returned could be close to but less than 1.

Any other thoughts or insight is appreciated.

