Let's say we have an IFrameAction interface with execute method. Sound class may implement it. Or i can create new class that dispatches a custom event on execute method. So i would dispatch event on any frame i want.

Instead of :
var sound:Sound = mSounds[mCurrentFrame];
if (sound) sound.play();

this:
var actions:Vector.<IFrameAction> = mActions[mCurrentFrame];
if(actions)
{
     for(bla bla) (actions[bla] as IFrameAction).execute();
}

I would do this by extending the MovieClip class but all properties are private.

Just had a case where i needed to place the stats in a fixed spot so it was visible. ie, not aligned to a corner.

Below is my mod to showStatsAt which adds and x & y arguments. Not the clearest code as you still have to pass in alignments (which then get ignored)

Perhaps just exposing mStatsDisplay with a getter so it can be done manually post initialisation?

Cheers.

``` Actionscript
 public function showStatsAt(hAlign:String="left", vAlign:String="top", scale:Number=1, x:Number = NaN, y:Number = NaN):void
        {
            if (mContext == null)
            {
                // Starling is not yet ready - we postpone this until it's initialized.
                addEventListener(starling.events.Event.ROOT_CREATED, onRootCreated);
            }
            else
            {
                if (mStatsDisplay == null)
                {
                    mStatsDisplay = new StatsDisplay();
                    mStatsDisplay.touchable = false;
                    mStage.addChild(mStatsDisplay);
                }

                var stageWidth:int  = mStage.stageWidth;
                var stageHeight:int = mStage.stageHeight;

                mStatsDisplay.scaleX = mStatsDisplay.scaleY = scale;

                if(!isNaN(x)) mStatsDisplay.x = x;
                else if (hAlign == HAlign.LEFT) mStatsDisplay.x = 0;
                else if (hAlign == HAlign.RIGHT) mStatsDisplay.x = stageWidth - mStatsDisplay.width; 
                else mStatsDisplay.x = int((stageWidth - mStatsDisplay.width) / 2);

                if(!isNaN(y)) mStatsDisplay.y = y;
                else if (vAlign == VAlign.TOP) mStatsDisplay.y = 0;
                else if (vAlign == VAlign.BOTTOM) mStatsDisplay.y = stageHeight - mStatsDisplay.height;
                else mStatsDisplay.y = int((stageHeight - mStatsDisplay.height) / 2);
            }

            function onRootCreated():void
            {
                showStatsAt(hAlign, vAlign, scale, x, y);
                removeEventListener(starling.events.Event.ROOT_CREATED, onRootCreated);
            }
        }
```
